<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 06 at 4:27PM CDT until August 06 at 4:45PM CDT by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 445 PM CDT
FOR NORTHERN TALLAPOOSA...SOUTHEASTERN CLEBURNE AND SOUTHEASTERN CLAY
COUNTIES...
At 427 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from Muscadine to near Ranburne to near Goldville, moving
east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Heflin, Lineville, Ashland, New Site, Fruithurst, Edwardsville,
Goldville, Barfield, Daviston, Cleveland Crossroads, Cragford,
Sweetwater Lake, Hackneyville, Lake Cleburne, Micaville, Motley and
Mellow Valley.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
